prompt:

Clean and snappy, lasting around 0.3 to 0.7 seconds.

Contain a mechanical spring or metallic release click, resembling the release of a toasterâ€™s spring-loaded tray.

Include a light pop or whoosh at the end to indicate the bread lifting up or launching.

The tone should feel cheerful and positive, suggesting successful toasting (not harsh or alarming).

Avoid harsh buzzes, alarms, or deep mechanical sounds.

Should work well in a cartoony or stylized cooking game, similar to Overcooked.

Stereo or mono, .wav format, sample rate 44.1kHz or higher.

Optional: Add a subtle spring coil recoil fading out for extra character.
